{
  prompt: """How do I check if every value in a sequence is less than a certain value."""

  solution: """
   [1 2 3 4 5 6] = sequence

   sequence
   If(IsAllLess(7) {Msg("all matches")} {Msg("not all matches")})
  """

  explicit: """
   [1 2 3 4 5 6] = sequence

   sequence
   If(Predicat: IsAllLess(Value: 7) Then:{
    Msg("all matches")
    } Else: {
      Msg("not all matches")}
   )
  """

  explanation: """
    The IsAllLess Shard is a Shard that can be used in the Predicate parameter of conditional Shards such as If and When. It will parse through
    a sequence and check if every element is lesser than the value stated in the Value parameter. If all elements are of lower value, it will return true,
    otherwise, it will return false. If comparing String datatypes, the Shard will compare values based on Lexicographical Order. 
    The value placed in the Value parameter must be of the same data type as the input.
  """

  tag: "  #General"
}